The England cricket team 's involvement with multi-billion-pound fraudster Allen Stanford -- has been defended by West Indies cricket legend Sir Curtly Ambrose .
Great fast bowler Ambrose was one of the West Indies stars when he flew by helicopter to the Lord 's nursery ground in 2008 to launch his five-year deal with England that ended with his arrest and subsequent 110-year jail sentence .
The ECB president Giles Clarke did not want to discuss the Stanford legacy .